Chris Hani died today 28 years ago. ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa will be laying a wreath at the annual ceremony in Ekurhuleni. Courtesy #DStv403  * Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Today marks 28 years since Chris Hani died. The ANC and its alliance partners -- the SACP and Cosatu -- are hosting a wreath-laying ceremony in Ekurhuleni. ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa, SACP Secretary-General Blade Nzimande and Hani's widow Mpho are expected to attend the event. Hani was shot by Polish immigrant Janus Walus outside his Boksburg home in 1993.